  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. Substituting &ndash;1 for <span class=\"italic\">x</span> in the equation that defines <span class=\"italic\">f</span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of negative 1 equals, the fraction with numerator, open parenthesis, negative 1, close parenthesis, squared, minus 6, times, open parenthesis, negative 1, close parenthesis, plus 3, and denominator negative 1 minus 1, end fraction\"></span>. Simplifying the expressions in the numerator and denominator yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"the fraction with numerator 1 plus 6, plus 3, and denominator negative 2\"></span>, which is equal to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"10 over negative 2\"></span> or &ndash;5.<p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and may result from misapplying the order of operations when substituting &ndash;1 for <span class=\"italic\">x</span>. <!--EndFragment--></p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
